    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A content creator wants to know how much a post could potentially spread on a social media app. Right now, they are estimating how far a post could reach after several levels of sharing, starting with a small number of people.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #1:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Creator.java</code>, calculate the potential number of people reached at three levels of sharing. Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.pow()</code> to raise each result to a new power, and store each value in its own variable.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #2:</strong> Call <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">drawResults()</code> once for each level, passing in the number reached at that level.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the <strong>Documentation</strong> tab ⬆️ for help using the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.pow()</code> method.\r\n</div>",
